Variable
 - A named piece of memory that you use to store specific types of data
 - format of variable declaration
	typename variable_name {initalizer_value}


Int
 - Stores decimals
 - Typically occupies 4 bytes or more in memory

Rules for variable names
- Variables must start with a letter or an underscore (but not a number)
- After the first letter, anything is exceptable
- Variables are case sensitive
- No spaces
- No special characters (e,g. ? or +), (with exception to underscores)


